Package: DTA70
Type: Package
Title: Real Diagnostic Test Accuracy Datasets for Methodology Research
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "DTA70", "Researcher",
      email = "researcher@example.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: A collection of 76 diagnostic test accuracy (DTA) datasets containing
    over 1,966 individual studies sourced from published meta-analyses, systematic
    reviews, and the Limsi-Cochrane DTA collection. Includes 19 curated datasets
    from high-quality meta-analyses and 57 Cochrane systematic reviews covering
    diverse medical conditions. Designed for researchers developing and testing
    meta-analytic methods, including bivariate models, HSROC models, and threshold
    effect models. All datasets include 2x2 contingency table data (TP, FP, FN, TN)
    from primary diagnostic accuracy studies. Represents one of the larger
    collections of ready-to-use DTA datasets available in R. See package
    documentation for detailed dataset descriptions, data sources, and usage examples.
